
[1]famine

   FAM'INE, n. [L. fames.]

   1. Scarcity of food; dearth; a general want of provisions sufficient
   for the inhabitants of a country or besieged place.

   There was a famine in the land. Gen. 26.

   2. Want; destitution; as a famine of the word of life.
